----------------------------------------- English=20
Version------------------------------------------

Job offer: Post-Doc or Research Engineer - 18 months CDD

As part of the R&D project Booster qaBot : Question Answering and=20
Chatbot, bringing together the companies The QACompany=20
<https://the-qa-company.com/>, Wikit <https://www.wikit.ai/> and the=20
Hubert Curien laboratory=20
<https://laboratoirehubertcurien.univ-st-etienne.fr/en/index.html>, we=20
are recruiting a post-doc or research engineer for a period of 18 months.

Context of the project

Conversational agents (chatbots) are increasingly used in all sectors to=20
provide quick and cheap assistance to users. By asking a question, the=20
user expresses his intention; this intention is recognized among a list=20
of intentions of the system; the system then gives its answer to the=20
user. Like any expert system, this technique has the advantage of=20
providing precise answers because they are prepared. The disadvantage is=20
that it requires a significant amount of time to design and maintain=20
conversational scenarios with the associated intentions. Question=20
Answering (QA) systems have appeared very recently, in particular to=20
query document databases. The user sends his question, and the system=20
answers by selecting a document and identifying the text answering the=20
question. The technique of QA systems requires less specific design=20
effort, but it currently requires very large training resources=20
(questions and answers in documents) which limits its adoption beyond=20
very large databases such as Wikipedia and for English.

The qaBot project focuses on automatic natural language processing (NLP)=20
and deep learning. Its objective is to bring to the market a mixed=20
approach combining Chatbot technology - provided by the Lyon-based=20
company Wikit <https://www.wikit.ai/> - and document-based Q&A=20
technology - developed by The QA Company <https://the-qa-company.com/>.=20
The scientific and academic part of the program is under the direction=20
of the Hubert Curien laboratory=20
<https://laboratoirehubertcurien.univ-st-etienne.fr/en/index.html> (with=20
the University of Saint-Etienne and the CNRS as main supervisors).

Missions

The recruited person will have to invest mainly on the scientific=20
support of the project on the aspects of the training of the models, for=20
specific and small data (few shots regimes), the study and the synthesis=20
of the recent works, and the implementation/evaluation of these. More=20
specifically, the scientific challenges identified are

  *

    Designing a powerful neural architecture with few-shot training data
    sets for the task of extractive question answering on specific domain=
s

  *

    Define metrics to evaluate the created chatbots. These metrics will
    be used to evaluate the systems during the project.

  *

    Rapidly adapt existing linguistic models to non-English languages.

  *

    Adapt the system to text corpora in specific formats (e.g. pdf or
    websites)

Required Skills

The candidate should have strong skills in Machine Learning (model=20
design, mastery of deep learning frameworks such as PyTorch/TensorFlow),=20
but also advanced skills in Python, a strong interest in textual data,=20
question answering and so-called Large Language Models (BERT, PaLM), as=20
well as overfitting and the application of the latter (in particular via=20
HuggingFace)

Additional information

The host site is the Hubert Curien laboratory=20
<https://laboratoirehubertcurien.univ-st-etienne.fr/en/index.html>, a=20
joint research unit (UMR 5516) of the Jean Monnet University of=20
Saint-Etienne, the Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique (CNRS)=20
and the Institut d'Optique Graduate School. It is composed of about 90=20
researchers, professors and lecturers, 20 engineers and administrative=20
staff and 130 PhD and post-doctoral students. Our research activities=20
are organized into two scientific departments: Optics, Photonics and=20
Surfaces and Computer Science, Security and Image. The Data Intelligence=20
team, in which the person recruited will work, is specialized in the=20
field of Machine Learning

The salary is flexible depending on the candidate's experience. The=20
candidate will have access to a workstation with a computer allowing the=20
use of the laboratory's computing cluster. The start of the contract is=20
planned for the beginning of January 2023. The laboratory is located on=20
the same campus as The QA Company <https://the-qa-company.com/>, thus=20
facilitating exchanges with the company's researchers and PhD student=20
involved in the project.

To apply, please send toantoine.gourru@univ-st-etienne.frand=20
francois.jacquenet@univ-st-etienne.fr: a detailed CV and a cover letter,=20
*as soon as possible*.


